socket io is complelety diff package 
not work with express directly 
express is also built on the top of http


- app (express server)   connect with    io (socket io server)   by  httpServer 

io - server
socket - single user

on - event listen
emit - event fire



ext - Echo API 



how clients communicate in real time.

I started with `socket.emit` to send messages to one client
Then I used `io.emit` to send messages to all clients
this sends messages back to the sender too


here `socket.broadcast.emit`come
It sends messages to everyone except the sender.
This is perfect for real-time chat systems.


Rooms let me group clients and send messages to specific groups.
It felt like creating mini chat groups inside the server.


While practicing, a question came to my mind:
How does the server know which user is in which room?
And if multiple servers are running,
how do they share this information efficiently?


This is where **adapters** come in
Adapters handle message routing and room management
The default in-memory adapter works fine for one server
But in multi-server setups, it cannot share room data


That’s why **Redis adapter** is needed
Redis acts as a shared memory for all servers.
It keeps track of rooms and which sockets belong where.
This ensures messages reach the right clients,
even if they are connected to different servers.


I practiced acknowledgements to confirm message delivery.
And built small apps to apply everything I learned.



